<TEXT>
Eight convicts armed with 
knives and homemade bombs escaped from a southern penal colony by 
taking hostage the penitentiarys superintendent and his wife 
police said today 
The hostages were released later 
Most of the escapees are serving terms for murder 
Police said the inmates barged into the chapel of the San Ramon 
Prison and Penal Farm and seized superintendent Leonito Narvaez and 
his wife as the couple attended Mass late Friday with other prison 
officials and prisoners 
The inmates then walked out the gates of the sprawling complex 
threatening to kill the hostages if guards tried to stop them 
police said 
Narvaez and his wife were released two hours later in a village 
several miles away 
Most inmates at the penal colony near Zamboanga City 540 miles 
southeast of Manila live with their families and are allowed to 
cultivate small farms within the complex 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

